#. Tag: title
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:11
#, no-c-format
msgid "&buildah; overview"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:12
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<link xlink:href=\"https://buildah.io/\">&buildah;</link> is tool for "
"building OCI-compliant container images. &buildah; can handle the following "
"tasks:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:18
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create containers from scratch or from existing images."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:23
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create an image from a working container or via Dockerfile."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:28
#, no-c-format
msgid "Build images in the OCI or &deng; image formats."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:33
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mount a working container's root file system for manipulation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:38
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the updated contents of a container's root file system as a file system "
"layer to create a new image."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:44
#, no-c-format
msgid "Delete a working container or an image and rename a local container."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:49
#, no-c-format
msgid "Compared to &deng;, &buildah; has several advantages:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:54
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The tool makes it possible to mount a working container's file system, so it "
"becomes accessible by the host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:60
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The process of building container images using &buildah; can be automated "
"via scripts by using &buildah;'s subcommands instead of a Containerfile or "
"Dockerfile."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:67
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Similar to &podman;, &buildah; does not require a daemon to run and can be "
"used by unprivileged users."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:73
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is possible to build images inside a container without mounting the "
"&docker; socket, which improves security."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:80
#, no-c-format
msgid "&podman; and &buildah;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:82
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Both &podman; and &buildah; can be used to build container images. While "
"&podman; makes it possible to build images using Dockerfiles, &buildah; "
"offers an expanded range of image building options and capabilities."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:89
#, no-c-format
msgid "&buildah; installation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:91
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To install &buildah;, run the command <command>sudo zypper in buildah</"
"command> . Run the command <command>buildah --version</command> to check "
"whether &buildah; has been installed successfully."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:98
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you already have &podman; installed and set up for use in rootless mode, "
"&buildah; can be used in an unprivileged environment without any further "
"configuration. If you need to enable rootless mode for &buildah;, run the "
"following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:105
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.user;sudo usermod --add-subuids 200000-201000 --add-subgids "
"200000-201000 $USER"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:107
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This command enables rootless mode for the current user. After running the "
"command, log out and log in again to enable the changes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:112
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The command above defines a range of local UIDs on the host, onto which the "
"UIDs allocated to users inside the container are mapped. Note that the "
"ranges defined for different users must not overlap. It is also important "
"that the ranges do not reuse the UID of any existing local users or groups. "
"By default, adding a user with the <command>useradd</command> command on "
"&slsa; &product-ga; automatically allocates subUID and subGID ranges."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:122
#, no-c-format
msgid "&buildah; in rootless mode"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:123
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In rootless mode, &buildah; commands must be executed in a modified user "
"namespace of the user. To enter this user namespace, run the command "
"<command>buildah unshare</command> . Otherwise, the <command>buildah mount</"
"command> command will fail."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:132
#, no-c-format
msgid "Building images with &buildah;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:134
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Instead of a special file with instructions, &buildah; uses individual "
"commands to build an image. Building an image with &buildah; involves "
"several steps: Run a container based on the specified image, edit the "
"container (install packages, configure settings, etc.), configure the "
"container options, and commit all changes into a new image. While this "
"process may include additional steps, such as mounting the container's file "
"system and working with it, the basic workflow logic remains the same."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:144
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following example can give you a general idea of how to build an image "
"with &buildah;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:150
#, no-c-format
msgid "Build image example"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:151
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"container=$(buildah from suse/sle15) <co xml:id=\"ctr\"/>\n"
"buildah run $container zypper up <co xml:id=\"run\"/>\n"
"buildah copy $container . /usr/src/example/ <co xml:id=\"copy\"/>\n"
"buildah config --workingdir /usr/src/example $container\n"
"buildah config --port 8000 $container\n"
"buildah config --cmd \"php -S 0.0.0.0:8000\" $container <co xml:id=\"config"
"\"/>\n"
"buildah config --label maintainer=\"Tux\" $container\n"
"buildah config --label version=\"0.1\" $container <co xml:id=\"label\"/>\n"
"buildah commit $container example <co xml:id=\"commit\"/>\n"
"buildah rm $container <co xml:id=\"rm\"/>\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:164
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Run a container (also called a working container) based on the specified "
"image (in this case, <literal>sle15</literal> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:170
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Run a command in the working container you just created. In this example, "
"&buildah; runs the <command>zypper up</command> command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:176
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Copy files and directories to the specified location in the container. In "
"this example, &buildah; copies the entire contents of the current directory "
"to <filename>/usr/src/example/</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:183
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>buildah config</command> commands specify container options. "
"These include defining a working directory, exposing a port, and running a "
"command inside the container."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:190
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>buildah config --label</command> command allows you to assign "
"labels to the container. This may include <literal>maintainer</literal> , "
"<literal>description</literal> , <literal>version</literal> , and so on."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:198
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create an image from the working container by committing all the "
"modifications."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-buildah-overview.xml:204
#, no-c-format
msgid "Delete the working container."
msgstr ""
